===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|thin|thin, thinne|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|þynne|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|þunnuz||thin|lang=gem-pro}}, (compare {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|þanjaną||to stretch, spread out|lang=gem-pro}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|ténh₂us||thin|lang=ine-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|tenw(ə)-||to pull, stretch|lang=ine-pro}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|thinner|thinnest}}

# Having little [[thickness]] or [[extent]] from one [[surface]] to its opposite.
#: '''''thin''' plate of metal''
#: '''''thin''' paper''
#: '''''thin''' board''
#: '''''thin''' covering''
# Very [[narrow]] in all diameters; having a [[cross section]] that is small in all directions.
#: '''''thin''' wire''
#: '''''thin''' string''
# Having little body fat or flesh; slim; slender; lean; gaunt.
#: '''''thin''' person''
# Of low [[viscosity]] or low specific [[gravity]], e.g., as is water compared to honey.
# [[scarce|Scarce]].
# {{golf}} Describing a poorly played [[golf]] shot where the ball is struck by the bottom part of the club head. See [[fat]], [[shank]], [[toe]].

